{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01NZpmXJvAawxU2GDU9GS4wD","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/*\n     2→ * Copyright (c), Eclipse Foundation, Inc. and its licensors.\n     3→ *\n     4→ * All rights reserved.\n     5→ *\n     6→ * This program and the accompanying materials are made available under the\n     7→ * terms of the Eclipse Distribution License v1.0, which is available at\n     8→ * https://www.eclipse.org/org/documents/edl-v10.php\n     9→ *\n    10→ * SPDX-License-Identifier: BSD-3-Clause\n    11→ */\n    12→package jakarta.tutorial.addressbook.web.util;\n    13→\n    14→import java.util.List;\n    15→\n    16→import jakarta.faces.application.FacesMessage;\n    17→import jakarta.faces.component.UIComponent;\n    18→import jakarta.faces.context.FacesContext;\n    19→import jakarta.faces.convert.Converter;\n    20→import jakarta.faces.model.SelectItem;\n    21→\n    22→public class JsfUtil {\n    23→    \n    24→    public static SelectItem[] getSelectItems(List<?> entities, boolean selectOne) {\n    25→        int size = selectOne ? entities.size() + 1 : entities.size();\n    26→        SelectItem[] items = new SelectItem[size];\n    27→        int i = 0;\n    28→        if (selectOne) {\n    29→            items[0] = new SelectItem(\"\", \"---\");\n    30→            i++;\n    31→        }\n    32→        for (Object x : entities) {\n    33→            items[i++] = new SelectItem(x, x.toString());\n    34→        }\n    35→        return items;\n    36→    }\n    37→    \n    38→    public static void addErrorMessage(Exception ex, String defaultMsg) {\n    39→        String msg = ex.getLocalizedMessage();\n    40→        if (msg != null && msg.length() > 0) {\n    41→            addErrorMessage(msg);\n    42→        } else {\n    43→            addErrorMessage(defaultMsg);\n    44→        }\n    45→    }\n    46→    \n    47→    public static void addErrorMessages(List<String> messages) {\n    48→        for (String message : messages) {\n    49→            addErrorMessage(message);\n    50→        }\n    51→    }\n    52→\n    53→    public static void addErrorMessage(String msg) {\n    54→        FacesMessage facesMsg = new FacesMessage(FacesMessage.SEVERITY_ERROR, msg, msg);\n    55→        FacesContext.getCurrentInstance().addMessage(null, facesMsg);\n    56→    }\n    57→\n    58→    public static void addSuccessMessage(String msg) {\n    59→        FacesMessage facesMsg = new FacesMessage(FacesMessage.SEVERITY_INFO, msg, msg);\n    60→        FacesContext.getCurrentInstance().addMessage(\"successInfo\", facesMsg);\n    61→    }\n    62→    \n    63→    public static String getRequestParameter(String key) {\n    64→        return FacesContext.getCurrentInstance().getExternalContext().getRequestParameterMap().get(key);\n    65→    }\n    66→    \n    67→    public static Object getObjectFromRequestParameter(String requestParameterName, Converter<Object> converter, UIComponent component) {\n    68→        String theId = JsfUtil.getRequestParameter(requestParameterName);\n    69→        return converter.getAsObject(FacesContext.getCurrentInstance(), component, theId);\n    70→    }\n    71→    \n    72→}\n    73→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01AGuLynqKbX6GBPbTJhnboR","session_id":"3d342aae-e137-4418-8b0e-e804e71f62e8","uuid":"03b7921b-ee51-4974-90ed-870c33b25e22"}
